\s2\sb120\lang2057\b\f2\fs28 Brief Description of Functionality\par
\pard{\*\pn\pnlvlcont\pnf1\pnindent0\pnstart1\pndec }
\li709\lang1036\b0\f1\fs24\par
\pard{\*\pn\pnlvlcont\pnf2\pnindent0\pnstart1\pndec }
\keepn\s3\lang1033\b\f2 Modular Design\par
\pard{\*\pn\pnlvlcont\pnf1\pnindent0\pnstart1\pndec }
\li709\lang1036\b0\f1\par
{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}The software has been developed to work on a modular basis allowing the user to perform at several levels of conversion. These can range from simple character set or exchange format translations using individual tables to full MARC format conversions using an entire \lquote cluster\rquote  of tables and rules.\par
{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}\par
{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}The Standalone batch version of USEMARCON only permits batch conversion runs, and all software associated with the creation, editing and testing of rules has been removed.\par
{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}\par
{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}The Standalone batch version reads all conversion parameters from an INI file. This INI file is a mandatory command line parameter to the program.\par
{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}\par
{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}As the program is performing its conversion, it display a running total of how many records have been read from the input file, and an approximate percentage of completion.\par
{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}\par
{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}Details of processing problems are stored in a report file and classified by the following error types: input format, MARC checking in input, character translation, coded data translation, conversion, MARC checking in output and building of the output MARC file.\par
{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}\par
{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}Diacritics and other extended characters are always displayed in hexadecimal code in order to allow users to check the accuracy of character translations.\par
{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}\par
{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}\par
\pard{\*\pn\pnlvlcont\pnf2\pnindent0\pnstart1\pndec }
