\s2\sb120\lang2057\b\f2\fs28 MARC Formats That May be Translated by USEMARCON\par
\pard{\*\pn\pnlvlcont\pnf1\pnindent0\pnstart1\pndec }
\li709\lang1036\b0\f1\fs24\par
{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}The USEMARCON program can only deal with input records compliant with the ISO 2709 standard for the exchange of bibliographic information. This format is commonly known as the MARC Communications or Exchange format. All output files produced by USEMARCON must also be fully compliant with ISO 2709. USEMARCON cannot therefore process data in formats which do not conform to this standard, for example, the German MAB or Dutch PICAPLUS formats.\par
{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}\par
{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}In order to assist the processing of data from a variety of sources, users are provided with the facility to specify many details of structure used for input and output files, including: blocking factors, use of segmentation characters, minimum size of usable data blocks and padding characters.\par
{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}\par
\pard{\*\pn\pnlvlcont\pnf2\pnindent0\pnstart1\pndec }
\s2\sb120\lang2057\b\f2\fs28 Conversions Available\par
\pard{\*\pn\pnlvlcont\pnf1\pnindent0\pnstart1\pndec }
\li709\lang1036\b0\f1\fs24\par
{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}The GUI version of the USEMARCON software provides rules files and related format conversion tables for the following conversions:\par
{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}\par
{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}UNIMARC to UKMARC \i (Bibliographic)\i0\par
{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}UKMARC to UNIMARC \i (Bibliographic)\par
\i0{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}\par
{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}UKMARC to UNIMARC \i (Authorities)\par
\i0{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}\par
{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}USMARC to UNIMARC \i (Bibliographic)\par
\i0{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}UNIMARC to USMARC \i (Bibliographic)\par
\i0{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}\par
{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}Other formats and conversion criteria have been developed by different organisations.\par
{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}\par
