{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}To run the USEMARCON Standalone Batch version:\par
{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}\par
{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}1) Open a command line window\par
{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}\par
{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}2) Change directory to where the USEMARCON executable was installed or refer to the program using a valid path\par
{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}\par
{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}3) Ensure that you have prepared a .ini file and that the associated conversion files are located as per the .ini file.\par
{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}\par
{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}4) Run the software like:\par
{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}   usemarcon <path>\\my.ini [input file] [output file]\par
{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}\par
{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}where path is the full or relative path name to where the .ini file is located.\par
{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}You can substitute my.ini for your actual ini file name.\par
{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}Input and output files are optional. If specified, they override the settings in the ini file. This could be used for example for batch processing of multiple files or creating a drag target on the desktop.\par
{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}\par
